SUBSTITUTE FOR
HOUSE BILL NO. 4663
A bill to amend 1998 PA 58, entitled
"Michigan liquor control code of 1998,"
(MCL 436.1101 to 436.2303) by adding section 1016.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF MICHIGAN ENACT:
1 Sec. 1016. Notwithstanding section 609(1) and R 436.1041 of
2 the Michigan Administrative Code, a licensee may donate a portion
3 of the profits generated from the licensee's license to an
4 organization that is not a licensee and that is exempt from
5 taxation under section 501(c) of the internal revenue code of 1986,
6 26 USC 501, if the licensee records its profits on its financial
7 records before making the donation allowed under this section. On
8 request, the licensee shall report its profits to the commission.
9 Notwithstanding section 609(1), if the organization receiving the
